Package: edr4r
Title: Client for OGC API - Environmental Data Retrieval (EDR)
Version: 0.2.0.9000
Authors@R:
    person("Kyle", "Onda", role = c("aut", "cre", "cph"),
           email = "konda@lincolninst.edu")
Description: A tidy R client for services implementing the OGC API -
    Environmental Data Retrieval ('EDR') standard with JSON discovery and
    'GeoJSON', 'CoverageJSON', or 'CSV' query responses. General purpose,
    but most of its real-world use is against in-situ monitoring networks
    (stream gauges, weather stations, snow and reservoir telemetry)
    that expose their stations and time series as EDR collections.
    Known working endpoints include the USGS waterdata OGC API and the
    Western Water Datahub. Provides cached capability and instance discovery,
    endpoint diagnostics, and query/parsing helpers for the locations, items,
    position, area, cube, radius, trajectory, and corridor query types.
    Supports bounded 'GeoJSON' pagination and finite sequential pulls for
    explicit sets of monitoring locations.
    Converts 'CoverageJSON' to tidy 'tibble' rows, parses 'CSV' as tibbles,
    and converts 'GeoJSON' to 'sf' objects.
